 from the life and well-being of the nonhuman world. By turning to such ancient ethnographies, we can uncover important models for confronting environmental crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEthnologistszGreecexHistory. 0aEthnologyzMediterranean RegionxHistory. 0aHuman ecologyzMediterranean Region. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh  aagriculture.  aalexander.  aancient greece.  aancient philosophy.  aanimals.  aanthropology.  aantiquity.  aclassical philosophy.  aclimate.  adiodorus siculus.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental crisis.  aenvironmental humanities.  aenvironmentalism.  aethnography.  agreek communities.  agreek.  aherodotus.  ahistory.  ahuman life.  alandscape.  anatural world.  anature.  anonfiction.  anonhuman life.  aplants.  awilderness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishz978311070483908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974814zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974814.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070483-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020